{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351633863,"sessionID":"ses_31c036c38ffeeD8S5Pofc6twWk","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fe69b6001B7GDCKGLHr1sh7","sessionID":"ses_31c036c38ffeeD8S5Pofc6twWk","messageID":"msg_ce3fe6040001zcyxG2PrqKHiJ5","type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete with 3 clean commits:\n\n1. **`b30b8b4`** — Added `.features.yml.bak` and `.features.yml.*.bak` patterns to `.gitignore` so backup files are never committed.\n\n2. **`84ef0ba`** — Added `backup.maxBackups` config option to `WomboConfig` (default: 5) with validation, enabling users to configure how many backups to retain.\n\n3. **`49357eb`** — Implemented the core feature in `saveFeatures()`:\n   - **Timestamped backups**: Before every write, copies the existing `.features.yml` to `.features.yml.YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SS.bak`\n   - **Backup rotation**: Keeps only the last N backups (configurable via `config.backup.maxBackups`, default 5), deleting oldest first\n   - **Atomic writes**: Uses write-to-tmp-then-rename pattern (matching `saveState`'s approach) to prevent corruption from interrupted writes\n\nAll three constraints from the spec are satisfied:\n- ✅ Keep only the last N backups (configurable, default 5)\n- ✅ Backups are gitignored\n- ✅ Must use atomic write (tmp + rename) like saveState","time":{"start":1773351633862,"end":1773351633862}}}
